OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FThe West says China makes  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ftoo much. Its workers      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fdisagree                   
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Ren Wenbing is reluctant to leave the  
OL,6, hollowed-out brick shell which was once
OL,7, a thriving factory in China's          
OL,8, manufacturing hub of Dongguan.         
OL,10,F"All the workers feel astonished," says
OL,11,Fthe 54-year-old as he points out where 
OL,12,Fhe once assembled furniture and where  
OL,13,Feveryone would gather to eat lunch.    
OL,15,FThe owner of the company has moved     
OL,16,Fproduction to South East Asia to cut   
OL,17,Fcosts. Mr Ren says he is owed more than
OL,18,F80,000 RMB ($11,000; #8,800) in        
OL,19,Fredundancy pay, which could take him   
OL,20,Fyears to earn.                         
